\section {Counterexample} \label{4}
\bigskip

\subsection {On The parallel of ${\mathfrak p} = {\mathfrak t}$}\
\bigskip

In \S2 we generalize \cite[Ch.VI,2.6]{Sh:c} to filters,
using the class of relevant ${\rm RSP}$'s $\bold r$ being 
closed under reduced powers (being a Horn class, see \ref{c7}).  
Can we generalize the result of
Malliaris-Shelah \cite{MiSh:998}?  It seems that we can give a counter-example.

For this we have to find
{\medskip\noindent}
\begin{enumerate}
\item[$(*)_1$]  $D$ a filter of $\lambda$ such that the partial order
  $N_1 = ({\mathbb Q},<)^\lambda/D$ satisfies ${\mathfrak p}^*(N_1) = 
\kappa_1 + \kappa_2 < \mu^+ \le {\mathfrak p}^*_{{\rm sym}}(N_1),\kappa_1 \ne
\kappa_2,(\kappa_1,\kappa_2) \in {\mathscr C}(N_1)$, so in fact
$N_1$ have no $(\theta_1,\theta_2)$-cut when $\theta_1
  = {\rm cf}(\theta_1) = \theta_2 \le \mu$ and when $\theta_\ell \ge \mu^+
  \wedge \theta_{3-\ell} \in \{0,1\}$
{\smallskip\noindent}
\item[$(*)_2$]  preferably: $\lambda = \mu$
{\smallskip\noindent}
\item[$(*)_3$]  or at least for some dense linear order $M_0$ there is a
 complete Boolean Algebra ${\mathfrak B}$ and a filter $D$ on ${\mathfrak B}$ such that
 $N_0 = M^{{\mathfrak B}}_0/D$ is as above.
\end{enumerate}
{\medskip\noindent}
We presently deal with the (main) case $\theta=\aleph_0$ 
and carry this out.  It
seems reasonable that we can prove, e.g. $T_{{\rm feq}}
\ntriangleleft_{{\rm rp}} T_{{\rm ord}}$ but we have not arrived to it.  In
\ref{s48} we say more; we can control the set of non-symmetric pre-cuts.

\begin{convention}
\label{b0}
$T_{{\rm ord}}$ is the first order theory of $({\mathbb Q},\le)$, see \ref{b7}(1)(d).
\end{convention}

